						               													<description>Life is Rolling Stones is a life simulation game that takes place over each player's &amp;quot;Junior&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Adult&amp;quot;, and &amp;quot;Senior&amp;quot; stage.  Each player has a starting character card, and will, after rolling, place a die in each of 4 colors on it: red (passion), blue (logic), yellow (lust), and green (harmony).  Each player also receives a hand of cards which represent their aspirations, and these cards will grant the player special in-game abilities and end-game scoring opportunities.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game takes place over 3 rounds, each with 3 turns.  Players draft turn order, with those going later receiving certain bonuses, and then draft life events from a public pool.  In addition to the chosen card, each player will have one life event &amp;quot;happen&amp;quot; to them from a blind draw.  Each round will also feature an event that will affect each of the players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Much of the game centers around &amp;quot;tipping&amp;quot; the dice.  For instance, if a card is to be placed into a player's tableau, you must try to place it next to the card that currently has the corresponding die on it; the die is then &amp;quot;tipped&amp;quot; onto the card, changing its value accordingly.  In the game's theme, the higher the value of a die, the more fulfilled a player is in that aspect of their life.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After 9 rounds, the player with the most points wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
